cs.RO, cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SY. 

The paper proposes a novel approach for long-term localization in a changing environment using 3D LiDAR, which is a common problem in robotics research. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.RO (Robotics). The paper also uses GPS and LiDAR to create a map of the environment, which involves computer vision techniques, making cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) another likely category. The paper also mentions the fusion of different kinds of odometers, which involves machine learning techniques, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) possible categories. Finally, the paper evaluates the algorithm on an unmanned ground vehicle, which involves control and systems engineering, making cs.SY (Systems and Control) a possible category as well.
